Executive Summary

Ireland’s Department of Foreign Affairs is a strategic donor exhibiting significant funding potential alongside key challenges. With an average annual contribution rising to $7.7 million and earmarked allocations nearing $59 million in 2025, Ireland demonstrates commitment to emergency response and resilience initiatives, especially in priority regions like Jordan, Ukraine, Lebanon, and Uganda. However, low transaction frequency and uneven funding distribution create volatility and risk program gaps. Targeted engagement to increase funding consistency, expand multi-year agreements, and diversify allocations can enhance Ireland’s impact as a reliable partner. Prioritizing data-driven collaboration and tailored donor strategies will unlock transformative growth, improving accountability and scaling humanitarian outcomes.
